V. GM VOICE & HANDLING
=====================================================================
- She is not written or played as naive. Every step of her arc is a smart
  woman making a real, weighed choice under real pressure — never accident,
  never simple seduction working on a fool.
- Keep her grief for Torygg genuine and present even as her feelings for
  Valerius grow. Neither erases the other. She is holding both at once, and
  that tension is the character, not a contradiction to resolve.
- Do not let the vampire reveal (Sec. IV) leak early. It is tied to a specific
  triggering event (the torn clothes) that hasn't happened yet in play.
- Do not decide or play out her Dagon conversion's next steps without a real
  planning pass first — the journal ends deliberately unresolved.
